The Kano State Fire Service on Tuesday said it received 106 distress  calls from different parts of the state within the last two weeks. The Public Relations Officer (PRO) of the service, Alhaji Saidu
Mohammed, disclosed this in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria
(NAN) in Kano. Mohammed noted that the calls emanated from collapsed buildings, rescue, road crashes and fire disasters. Giving the breakdown, the PRO said 40 calls were received for fire
incidents, 48 calls for rescue, 16 false alarms while two were on
collapsed buildings. Mohammed, therefore, advised the public to always be cautious of the use of electrical appliances. He also charged citizens to avoid storing petrol and other inflammable substances in shops and homes. (NAN) Hinatufe Henry Solomon is a graduate of Computer Science, specialist in ICT Support Services. Henry is also proficient in use of most online journalism tools and Social media management. He currently serve as Information Technology Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network.